  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why don't girls talk to me, but talk to everyone else?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're feeling this way. Building connections can sometimes be challenging, but there are several factors that might be influencing your experiences. Here are a few possibilities and suggestions that might help:\n\n1. **Self-Confidence:** Confidence plays a significant role in social interactions. If you're feeling unsure of yourself, it might come across unintentionally. Working on building your self-esteem can make you feel more comfortable when approaching others.\n\n2. **Communication Skills:** Effective communication involves both speaking and listening. Try to engage in conversations by showing genuine interest in what others are saying, asking open-ended questions, and sharing about yourself in a balanced way.\n\n3. **Body Language:** Non-verbal cues like eye contact, smiling, and open posture can make a big difference in how approachable you seem. Being aware of your body language can help make interactions more positive.\n\n4. **Common Interests:** Finding shared interests or activities can provide a natural foundation for conversations and connections. Whether it's a hobby, sport, or a particular topic, common ground can make interactions smoother.\n\n5. **Approachability:** Sometimes, subtle signals can affect how others perceive your willingness to engage. Ensuring you seem open and friendly can encourage others to initiate conversations with you.\n\n6. **Feedback from Trusted Friends:** Sometimes, getting honest feedback from friends or people you trust can provide insights into any behaviors or habits you might not be aware of. They can offer constructive advice tailored to your specific situation.\n\n7. **Patience and Persistence:** Building meaningful connections often takes time. Don't get discouraged if things don't change immediately. Keep putting yourself out there and stay open to meeting new people.\n\n8. **Reflect on Past Interactions:** Think about past conversations and interactions. Are there patterns or specific situations where things didn't go as you'd hoped? Understanding these can help you make adjustments.\n\n9. **Seek Support if Needed:** If you find that these feelings are significantly affecting your well-being, it might be helpful to talk to a counselor or therapist. They can provide personalized strategies and support.\n\nRemember, everyone has unique qualities that make them interesting and valuable. Focusing on your strengths and staying open to growth can enhance your interactions and help you build the connections you desire.",
